# Universal Data Validation Framework - Implementation Walkthrough

## Overview

Successfully implemented a plugin-based universal data validation framework that supports 5 comparison scenarios with interactive HTML reports and drill-down visualizations.

## What Was Built

### 🏗️ Architecture

Implemented a clean plugin-based architecture with three main layers:

1. **Adapter Layer**: Handles data loading from different sources
2. **Core Layer**: Orchestrates validation and comparison logic
3. **Reporting Layer**: Generates interactive HTML and CSV reports

### 📦 Components Created

#### Adapters (4 files)

- [base_adapter.py](file:///Users/kkrishna/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-InfobloxInc/PycharmProjects/infoblox-DE/1UniversalFramework/universal-validator/adapters/base_adapter.py) - Abstract base class defining adapter interface
- [file_adapter.py](file:///Users/kkrishna/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-InfobloxInc/PycharmProjects/infoblox-DE/1UniversalFramework/universal-validator/adapters/file_adapter.py) - Handles CSV, JSON, Parquet, Excel files
- [table_adapter.py](file:///Users/kkrishna/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-InfobloxInc/PycharmProjects/infoblox-DE/1UniversalFramework/universal-validator/adapters/table_adapter.py) - Handles Redshift database tables
- [datasource_adapter.py](file:///Users/kkrishna/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-InfobloxInc/PycharmProjects/infoblox-DE/1UniversalFramework/universal-validator/adapters/datasource_adapter.py) - Handles Tableau TWBX files

#### Core Engine (3 files)

- [validator.py](file:///Users/kkrishna/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-InfobloxInc/PycharmProjects/infoblox-DE/1UniversalFramework/universal-validator/core/validator.py) - Main orchestrator coordinating the workflow
- [comparator.py](file:///Users/kkrishna/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-InfobloxInc/PycharmProjects/infoblox-DE/1UniversalFramework/universal-validator/core/comparator.py) - Comparison engine with all validation checks
- [reporter.py](file:///Users/kkrishna/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-InfobloxInc/PycharmProjects/infoblox-DE/1UniversalFramework/universal-validator/core/reporter.py) - Report generator for CSV and HTML

#### Utilities (2 files)

- [helpers.py](file:///Users/kkrishna/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-InfobloxInc/PycharmProjects/infoblox-DE/1UniversalFramework/universal-validator/utils/helpers.py) - Common functions for comparison and path resolution
- [html_template.py](file:///Users/kkrishna/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-InfobloxInc/PycharmProjects/infoblox-DE/1UniversalFramework/universal-validator/utils/html_template.py) - Interactive HTML template with Chart.js

#### Entry Point & Configuration

- [main.py](file:///Users/kkrishna/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-InfobloxInc/PycharmProjects/infoblox-DE/1UniversalFramework/universal-validator/main.py) - CLI interface with argument parsing
- [example_validations.yaml](file:///Users/kkrishna/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-InfobloxInc/PycharmProjects/infoblox-DE/1UniversalFramework/universal-validator/config/example_validations.yaml) - Example configurations for all 5 scenarios

---

## Key Features Implemented

### ✅ 5 Comparison Scenarios

1. **File ↔ Redshift Table**: CSV/JSON/Parquet/Excel to database table
2. **Table ↔ Table**: Redshift table to table comparison
3. **File ↔ File**: Any file format to any file format
4. **DataSource ↔ DataSource**: TWBX to TWBX comparison
5. **DataSource ↔ Table**: TWBX to Redshift table

### ✅ Comprehensive Validation Checks

Migrated and enhanced all validation logic from your existing code:

- **Record Count Check**: Compares total row counts
- **Column Count Check**: Identifies missing/extra columns
- **Duplicate Detection**: Finds duplicate primary keys
- **Null Analysis**: Detects null values per column
- **Empty String Detection**: Identifies empty strings
- **Data Value Comparison**: Row-by-row or PK-based comparison with type coercion

### ✅ Interactive HTML Reports

Created rich HTML reports with:

- **Summary Dashboard**: Visual cards showing pass/fail metrics
- **Pie Chart**: Overall status distribution (Pass/Fail/Skip)
- **Bar Charts**: Validation type breakdown
- **Column Analysis Chart**: Horizontal bar chart showing top 20 culprit columns
- **Drill-Down Tables**: 
  - Failed checks table (sortable, searchable, filterable)
  - Passed checks table
  - All results table
- **Collapsible Sections**: Clean organization with expand/collapse
- **DataTables Integration**: Search, sort, paginate through results
- **Chart.js Visualizations**: Interactive charts with hover tooltips

### ✅ Configuration-Driven Approach

YAML-based configuration supporting:

- Multiple validations in single file
- Relative path resolution from project root
- Environment variable support for credentials
- Optional parameters (sheet names, JSON orientation, etc.)
- Per-validation output directories

